==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*ἀρχή / archē / ar-khay'

===Etymology===
*From [[ἄρχομαι]] {{GG|756}}; (properly abstract) a commencement, or (concrete) chief (in various applications of order, time, place or rank): 

===Noun===
'''ἀρχή'''

# A [[beginning]], [[corner]], (at the, the) [[first]] (estate), [[magistrate]], [[power]], [[principality]], [[principle]], [[rule]].

